<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="63" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="63">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="63">The cercus is more or less triangular, bordered by some strong marginal bristles that are strongly flattened or truncate. All cercus have one or two large inside bristles near the dorsal border. The postgonite is broad and the tip is bifid. The tip of the phallus is ventrally denticulate and the hypandrium is a simple tube.</paragraph>
